<H2>School</h2>
<h3>School Life in the Netherlands: </h3>
<p>Please note that school holidays in the Netherlands differ depending on their geographic location: North, Centre or South. As a result some of the information below may differ from region to region. Interests like playing a musical instrument and playing sports are things the students do in their free time, after school, in the village or town they live in or nearby.</p>

<h3>School Day </h3>
<p>In Holland school starts at about 08.30 a.m. and finishes at about 3.00 p.m. although<br />
  this will vary according to each student's timetable. Most students go to school by<br />
  bicycle or by public transport. There are almost no school buses. At school all students<br />
  learn 4 languages; Dutch, English, French and sometimes German. Other subjects at<br />
  school are Mathematics, Science, Geography and History.</p>
  
<h3>School Types </h3>
<p>Secondary school is divided into three levels: VMBO, HAVO, VWO. Exchange students are normally placed in the middle or higher levels, as VMBO is geared towards vocational learning.</p>

<h3>School Syllabus </h3>
<p>The syllabus varies from school to school, as the majority of schools are a mix of all three levels.</p>

